# = Rupl (RUby Personal Locator)
# Copyright (c) 2007 Jonathan S. Garvin (http://www.5valleys.com)
#
# == Description
# Rupl is a ruby libarary written for the GPS Enabled devices running
# the Maemo operating system for the purpose of providing a convienent
# method for Ruby applications to
# * use the built in GPS receiver to retrieve location data
# * trigger events based on movement or proximity to user defined
#   locations
# * provide common convenience functions for GPS related measurements
#   and calculations.
#
# Rupl has only been tested on the Nokia N810 Internet Tablet. The goal
# however is for Rupl to run on any GPS enabled device running the Maemo
# operating system, including the N900 phone.